Description: Nagios status monitor which takes place in systray or on desktop
 Nagstamon is a Nagios status monitor which takes place in systray or
 on desktop (GNOME, KDE) as floating statusbar to inform you in
 realtime about the status of your Nagios and some of its derivatives monitored network.
 It allows to connect to multiple Nagios, Icinga, Opsview, Centreon, Op5Monitor,
 Checkmk Multisite, Thruk, Zabbix and Zenoss servers. Events could be handled by instant access to failed hosts/services.

